result.name: Wah On Restaruant

reviews.text:
above average local cha chan tang.
friendly staff and good service.
lots of food choices.
had the deep fried chicken with their signature curry sause and the sause is really nice. 
their best dish is the deep fried chicken thigh with curry sause but its sold out.. so be there early if you want to get it! :)
The French toast is awesome (@ HKD21). Authentically Hong Kong style
Acceptable food quality but pricey

My favourite Hong Kong style budget restaurent around that area.  Seating is a bit tight and you cannot expect the environment of a pricy restaurent.  Will be crowded during lunch time. Good for a quick meal with good selection of properly cooked food items. HK style milk tea is of good standard...i.e. not plain and taste just like condenced milk in water.  Friendly staff.

Food was tasty but not enjoyable due to crowded space and small table.  Besides, you would feel that the waitress was pushing for a fast turnover and also keeping people waiting outside the entrance and telling them that table would be ready very soon.

reviews.text: 鮮茄牛粉幾好食，地方比較細，lunch要早d到，唔係就要等位
Lunch 豬扒啲肉好腍身又入味 👍👍👍  牛筋腩 D筋腍得嚟仲有彈性好黏嘴 正 👍👍👍D腩煮腍啲仲好 不過都好夠味  仲有一個鮑汁撈粗好鬼好食 👍👍👍  個蠔仔撈粗 都唔錯  下次要食雞髀 好似好多人嗌 仲要試埋嗰個咖哩腩飯  🥂
味道不錯，午飯時間人山人海，宜早幫襯。
